[[Image:Monkey batu.jpg|thumb|A monkey]]
==English==

===Pronunciation===
*mŭngki, /ˈmʌŋki/, /<tt>"mVNki</tt>/

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

# Any of several members of the [[infraorder]] ''[[Simiiformes]]'' of [[primate]]s, generally smaller than the [[ape]]s, and distinguished from them by having a [[tail]].
# (''English [[slang]] term'') five hundred pounds [[Sterling]].
# Origin. Sanskrit [[Kapi]]. From this Greek [[kepos]] leading to monkey. Also from [[Kapi]] with  first letter mute alteration we get Old Norse [[api]], Old English [[apa]], Old High German [[affo]], Welsh [[epa]] and Irish [[apa]] “ape”.

